<br>
He even had her take classes with the other students of magic in the temple to learn how her magic related to it, but how different it was also.  She learned that she could raise the ability of the casters and also make their ability to cast last much longer.  Once they discovered this gift she had to stop taking the classes.  The casters all wanted her to stay but she was wearing herself out in helping them.  So he spent an afternoon just explaining why she was needed for other uses too.<br>
<br>
Brenton told her that many casters would want her to only help them with their stamina in being able to casts and eventually would drain her if she allowed them too.  Playing one song over and over again would only limit her talent and eventually make her want to stop working with them all together.<br>
<br>
“If you want to your most effective you must learn to blend together all the talents that you have and temper them to the situation that you are facing.  You will learn that there are people that have no knowledge of what you are capable of and they will limit you if you allow them.&quot;  He looked into her violet eyes to make sure that she understood what he was saying.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Your talent is too strong to be used for one purpose only so learn to use all aspects of it.  Also, we will be bringing in people to teach you to defend yourself because there will be times that you must keep yourself safe because others may not.”  He smiled at the disdain her eyes showed at that revelation.<br>
